<br>
In my case I am running two computers so I can play a mage and a cleric (figured cleric is pretty much hands off after a while, pop upo heal, med, repeat)<br>
<br>
Someone told me a chanter makes a great partner too.  <br>
<br>
Thoughts?<br>
<br>
Serene<br>
<br>
Vazaelle<br>
(I am wondering how many people are going to stick with thgis new server) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umanchyman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>manchyman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#333333>(1/5/01 2:51:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   partner</span><hr size=1> I usually partner with a warrior friend but I like<br>
druids for the sow, tp and kiting...<br>
The best two man team I ever had was with another<br>
magi at lvl 36. <br>
We would just ping pong mobs back and forth. The<br>
dmg was awesome.<br>
<br>
Manchy Man <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uteldivagrimleux.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teldiva GrimLeux</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/kimmi_sc/tel_s_eye.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#333333>(1/5/01 3:44:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/kimmi_sc/teldiva3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: partner</span><hr size=1> Mages and Necros make for a pretty good duo too when fear kiting.  It's pretty mana efficient and the pair can easily take on many more mobs than a single mage can solo. <p><img src=http://www.geocities.com/kimmi_sc/teldiva_grimleux.jpg>
 <BR>Mage of the 50th season<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubixt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bixt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(1/5/01 3:45:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   go with...</span><hr size=1> For the least downtime, chanter and either mage or necro, necro is a little better. Only problem is deciding who pulls <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Ycore</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(1/5/01 4:23:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Easy choice</span><hr size=1> My favorite partner is a Shaman.  Whip out a good earth pet, have shammy slow and dot the mob, and then just let the pet beat it to death.  With slow on, my 51 earth pet can solo dar knights with 40% health left in seb.  Stack on a Dot from the shammy and he even does better.  Also, their str/agi buffs do wonders for the pets dmg output.<br>
<br>
Ycore Rixle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueadar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(1/5/01 6:26:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Easy choice</span><hr size=1> Depends where you are.<br>
<br>
Outside:  Mage and Necro.  Mage and Wiz work well too.<br>
<br>
Inside:  Mage and Shaman.  Done Mage and Necro before, not bad, was better with the shammy.<br>
<br>
<br>
I usually hunt outside with a mage/necro/wizard team outside.  Wizzie pulls and snares, Necro fears.  Working together we can handle trains in Skyfire and BW.  Has to be the best outside set up I have ever had. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unefariusgnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nefarius Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 331<br> <font color=#333333>(1/5/01 6:59:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Easy choice</span><hr size=1> Mage and necro can be pretty powerful indoors as well, in the right places. We lose fear, but with screaming terror, charm undead, and my sheer firepower the two of us broke and held the sage room at level 44. That's four blue /con mobs at once, three of which were wizards.<br>
<br>
Outdoors the mage always pulls. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  The necro has to constantly cast a variety of spells like fears, dots, engulfing darkness, etc, so they end up needing to med more. When pulling Seafuries I would pull with Malisement, put a couple nukes into the clops then sit down and med until it was dead. Then she'd med while I went for another pull. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 47th Trial<i><br>Member of Silmindo, Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Zebanar</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(1/7/01 4:47:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Shaman all the way..</span><hr size=1> Shamans are hands down the best indoors to group with. With a shaman, I can take down Icewell mobs, sure it takes multiple pets, but talk about amazing stuff. I doubt any other duo could do this. Perhaps a cleric/warrior, but even that I think would be close.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=waldenawildfyre>Waldena Wildfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#333333>(1/7/01 8:15:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shaman all the way..</span><hr size=1> Good partners for mages:<br>
 Another mage<br>
 Nerco<br>
 Shaman<br>
 Chanter<br>
These seem to be the best, but:<br>
 Druid<br>
