<br>
I magician is a killing machine but he (or she I will use he here for simplicity) lacks a few abilities.  He does not travel well.  He can not split a spawn.  He can not heal.  He can not handle more that one MOB at a time. Etc.<br>
<br>
Travel:  A druid is the best traveler in the game and a the wizard gets ports.<br>
<br>
Spliting a spawn:  A druid and a ranger has harmony.  Both also have snare.<br>
<br>
Healing:  The best healer is a cleric.  A cleric can keep your pet alive.  And a living fire pet will win.  The magician just have to keep the MOB off the cleric.  Druids, shaman, and to a lesser extent rangers and paladins can heal also.<br>
<br>
Crowd control:  The enchanter is the best crowd controler bar none.<br>
<br>
Buffs:  The enchanter with his damage shield, speed buffs and mob debuffs is a great partner.  The shaman also has some good buffs and debuffs.<br>
<br>
And what about the necro?  They can do all of the above but never quite as good as the other classes.  I have had good luck with a straight warrior as well, even at half hps he had twice as many as me.<br>
<br>
Everyone brings something to the table and you will always be stronger as a duo over going solo.  I personally have had great luck pairing with a druid, enchanter, cleric, wizard, necro, ranger and a warrior.  I have not found any class that is &quot;useless&quot; and I am always amazed at how well the classes are balance.<br>
<br>
So try out a few classes and then choose.  I have never tried a shadow knight or teamed with one but I am sure they would be interesting and bring a lot to the pair.  Good luck.<br>
<br>
